>Well, it's really unrealistic to think that a company can keep something
>like an operating system a secret until 90 days before it comes out.  
>Developers, at the very least, have to know about it before hand.  While
>neither MS nor IBM officially preannounces things years in advance, both
>of them are rather vocal about what they're working on.  Don't buy the line 
